						<summary>

						<p>South wall of the Nīlaviśālākshi-ammaṉ shrine in the same temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Tribhº Rājarājadēva Rājarāja III: Year 15 = 1237 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription is damaged, so several details are lost.</p>						

						<p>It appears to record a sale of land in connection with a certain consecration ceremony to some persons like Periyāṉ Pērayaṉ of a certain <hi rend="italic">nāḍu</hi> (not specified) by Paḷḷi-bhaṭṭaṉ Śōḻaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Periṅgūrp-pērayaṉ, a resident of Śiṟṟiṅgūr, a <hi rend="italic">brahmadēyam.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
